"{\"uid\": \"metro.co.uk-2024-08-05-olympian-breaks-world-record-twice-within-a-minutes-21364114\", \"text\": \"Poland's Aleksandra Miroslaw managed to break her speed climbing record twice within just 16 minutes at theParisOlympics.  The Olympic sport climbing events got underway on Monday having first been introduced to the games in Tokyo three years ago.  Two-time world champion Miroslaw is one of the favourites in the women's speed event and held both the world and Olympic record going into Paris.  Follow\\u00a0Metro.co.uk's live blog for updates from the Paris 2024 Olympics  And her rivals will be fearing her even more after the Pole broke her record not once but twice during the qualification heats.  In her first run, the 30-year-old blitzed up the climbing wall in a time of 6.21 seconds - 0.03 seconds quicker than the previous world record.  As it turns out, Miroslaw was just warming up, as just 16 minutes later she set a staggering time of 6.06 seconds during her second climb.  FENOMENALNA ALEKSANDRA MIRSO\\u00c5\\u0081AW! \\\"\\u00f0\\u009d\\u0090\\u0092\\u00cc\\u0081\\u00f0\\u009d\\u0090\\u0091\\u00f0\\u009d\\u0090\\u0094\\u00f0\\u009d\\u0090\\u0081\\u00f0\\u009d\\u0090\\u0080\\\" \\u00f0\\u009d\\u0090\\u0091\\u00f0\\u009d\\u0090\\u0084\\u00f0\\u009d\\u0090\\u008a\\u00f0\\u009d\\u0090\\u008e\\u00f0\\u009d\\u0090\\u0091\\u00f0\\u009d\\u0090\\u0083\\u00f0\\u009d\\u0090\\u0094 \\u00f0\\u009d\\u0090\\u0092\\u00cc\\u0081\\u00f0\\u009d\\u0090\\u0096\\u00f0\\u009d\\u0090\\u0088\\u00f0\\u009d\\u0090\\u0080\\u00f0\\u009d\\u0090\\u0093\\u00f0\\u009d\\u0090\\u0080\\u00e2\\u009d\\u0097\\u00f0\\u009f\\u0098\\u008d\\u00f0\\u009f\\u0094\\u00b4\\u00f0\\u009f\\u0093\\u00b2 Ogl\\u00c4\\u0085daj igrzyska w TVP \\u00e2\\u0096\\u00b6\\u00ef\\u00b8\\u008fhttps://t.co/6ZjJTzbuyBpic.twitter.com/MujNfCFY4V  That obviously saw her seeded first for the elimination heats where she easily beat South Africa's Aniya Holding with a (relatively sluggish) time of 6.10 seconds.  She will now take on Spain's Leslie Romero in Wednesday's quarter-final, with the semi-finals and final following shortly after that.  Though she set the inaugural Olympic record in Tokyo, Miroslaw left Japan without a medal after finishing fourth, with Janja Garnbret of Slovenia winning gold.  There is British interest in the climbing too, with Toby Roberts and Hamish McArthur through to the semi-finals of the men's boulder and lead event, with the former expected to be in medal contention.  For more stories like this,check our sport page.  Follow Metro Sport for the latest news onFacebook,TwitterandInstagram.  ArrowMORE:Referee forced off after heavy collision during Spain v Morocco Olympic semi-final  ArrowMORE:BBC viewers convinced legendary comedian is commentating Olympics gymnastics  ArrowMORE:Olympic star removed from athletes' village due to 'inappropriate' behaviour  Punchy analysis, transfer talk and more from Metro's football experts, sent straight to your inbox every week.  Let us know which team you support.Close  This site is protected by reCAPTCHA and theGoogle Privacy PolicyandTerms of Serviceapply. Your information will be used in line with ourPrivacy Policy  Punchy analysis, transfer talk and more from Metro's football experts, sent straight to your inbox every week.  Let us know which team you support.Close  This site is protected by reCAPTCHA and theGoogle Privacy PolicyandTerms of Serviceapply. Your information will be used in line with ourPrivacy Policy\"}"